                               WAIVER OF LIABILITY, RELEASE, ASSUMPTION OF RISK & INDEMNITY AGREEMENT
       IT IS THE PURPOSE OF THIS AGREEMENT FOR THE PARTICIPANT (AND PARTICIPANT'S PARENT(S)/GUARDIAN(S), IF
       APPLICABLE) TO EXEMPT, WAIVE AND RELIEVE RELEASEES FROM LIABILITY FOR PERSONAL INJURY, PROPERTY
       DAMAGE, AND WRONGFUL DEATH, INCLUDING IF CAUSED BY NEGLIGENCE, INCLUDING THE NEGLIGENCE, IF ANY, OF ANY
       RELEASEES."Releasees" include USA Hockey, Inc., its affiliate associations, local associations, member teams, event hosts, other
       participants, coaches, officials, sponsors, advertisers, and each of them, their officers, directors, agents and employees.For and in
       consideration of the undersigned Participant's registration with USA Hockey, Inc., its affiliates, local associations and member teams (all
       referred to together as USAH) and being allowed to participate in USAH events and member team activities, Participant (and the
       parent(s) or legal guardian(s) of Participant, if applicable) waives, releases and relinquishes any and all claims for liability and cause(s)
       of action, including for personal injury, property damage or wrongful death occurring to Participant, arising out of participation in USAH
       events, member team activities, the sport of ice hockey, and/or activities incidental thereto, whenever or however they occur and for
       such period said activities may continue, and by this agreement any such claims, rights, and causes of action that Participant (and
       Participant's parent(s) or legal guardian(s), if applicable) may have are hereby waived, released and relinquished, and Participant (and
       parent(s)/guardian(s), if applicable) does(do) so on behalf of my/our and Participant's heirs, executors, administrators and
       assigns.Participant (and Participant's parent(s)/guardian(s), if applicable) acknowledges, understands and assumes all risks relating to
       ice hockey and any member team activities, and understands that ice hockey and member team activities involve risks to Participant's
       person including bodily injury, partial or total disability, paralysis and death, and damages which may arise therefrom and that I/we have
       full knowledge of said risks. These risks and dangers may be caused by the negligence of the Participant or the negligence of others,
       including the "Releasees" identified above. These risks and dangers include, but are not limited to, those arising from participating with
       bigger, faster and stronger participants, and these risks and dangers will increase if Participant participates in ice hockey and member
       team activities in an age group above that which Participant would normally participate in. Participant (and Participant's
       parent(s)/guardian(s), if applicable) further acknowledges that there may be risks and dangers not known to us or not reasonably
       foreseeable at this time. Participant (and Participant's parent(s)/guardian(s), if applicable) acknowledge, understand and agree that all
       of the risks and dangers described throughout this agreement, including those caused by the negligence of Participant and/or others,
       are included within the waiver, release and relinquishment described herein. Participant (and participant's parent(s)/guardian(s), if
       applicable) acknowledges, understands and assumes the risks, if any, arising from the conditions and use of ice hockey rinks and
       related premises and acknowledges and understands that included within the scope of this waiver and release is any cause of action
       (including any cause of action based on negligence) arising from the performance, or failure to perform maintenance, inspection,
       supervision or control of said areas and for the failure to warn of dangerous conditions existing at said rinks, for negligent selection of
       certain Releasees, or negligent supervision or instruction by any Releasee.As a condition of registration and membership in USA
       Hockey and participation in USAH events and member team activities, Participant (and Participant's parent(s)/guardian(s), if applicable)
       agrees to abide by and be bound under the playing rules and rules and regulations of USA Hockey, including the By-Laws of USA
       Hockey and the mandatory dispute resolution, discipline and arbitration provisions, as currently published in the USA Hockey Annual
       Guide. Copies of the USA Hockey Bylaws, including the mandatory dispute resolution, discipline and arbitration clauses, are available
       from the USA Hockey offices or may be found at www.usahockey.com/annualguide. Any dispute, claim or cause of action regarding the
       terms of this agreement or subject matter hereof shall be brought (i) individually, without resort to any form of class or collective action,
       and without joinder or consolidation of claims of third parties, and (ii) exclusively in the manner provided in the rules of USA Hockey
       (including, without limitation USA Hockey Bylaw 10) to the extent applicable.As further consideration for registration and participation in
       USAH events and member team activities, Participant (and the parent(s) or legal guardian(s) of participant, if applicable), hereby (1)
       consents and agrees that USAH, its licensees and designees may make video and/or audio recordings of and/or otherwise film,
       photograph or memorialize some or all of Participant's participation in such events and activities, and (2) grants to USAH, its licensees,
       designees, successors and assigns, a worldwide, perpetual, irrevocable, fully-paid, royalty-free, transferable and sublicenseable right
       and license to use, copy and disseminate Participant's image and personal attributes, and to modify and present same in any form,
       manner and media, now known or hereafter devised, for any purpose whatsoever.If the law in any controlling jurisdiction renders any
       part of this agreement unenforceable, the remainder of this agreement shall nevertheless remain enforceable to the full extent, if any,
       allowed by controlling law. This agreement affects your legal rights, and you may wish to consult an attorney concerning this
       agreement.Participant (and Participant's parent(s)/guardian(s), if applicable) agree if any claim for Participant's personal injury or
       wrongful death is commenced against any Releasee, he/she shall defend, indemnify and save harmless Releasees from any and all

                                                                                 Transfer-price:        112 EUR
                                                                                Child seat fees:          4 EUR

                                                                 Free cancellation service fees:          4 EUR
                                                                              Total amount:         126 EUR
                                                                                     Prepaid:       126 EUR
                                                                               Pay to driver:           0 EUR

Instruction
Contacts
In case of airport delays upon arrival call your driver. The phone number of your driver will be sent by email and SMS.
In case of emergency call +44 (2080) 68 28 01 (charges apply) or +7 (499) 404 12 22 (Viber). Spare phone +7 (499) 550 02 11
(charges apply).
Changes and canceling
In order to make changes or cancel the transfer, go to the Personal Account by clicking on the link in the confirmation email.
You can make changes to the booking until 01:15 Jul.10 (local time of the transfer country). If you failed to do it on time, contact
us. We will try to help, but we can not guarantee that we will be able to change the booking parameters so close to the beginning
of the transfer.
You have purchased the cancellation service, so you can cancel your booking with the full refund of transfer costs anytime before
the trip - until 10.07.2019 17:15 (local time). If canceled, only 4 EUR will be withheld.
Meeting
Your driver will be waiting for you after the customs and luggage claim holding a sign with a name specified in the booking.
Meeting point
Meeting point is at the exit, outside the airport building.
Waiting time
Your driver will wait for one hour after scheduled flight arrival. In case of a delay up to 30 minutes, he will adjust the beginning of
waiting time. In case of a delay more than 30 minutes, you should contact your driver and negotiate extra waiting time at an
additional cost.
If your flight arrives earlier, please contact your driver.
Note
Inform us if you are travelling with children, animals or special luggage in advance. Lack of this information can cause transfer cancellation.
Special luggage includes the following objects: skis, snowboards, bicycles, wheelchairs and also suitcases when the sum of its three
dimensions is over 158 cm.
Pay attention that all deviations from the route of your journey and stops are paid additionally.

HSBC Creditor Insurance Protection
Mortgage, Line of Credit and Demand Loan
Important Information

This is opticnal group creditor insurance providing coverage in the event of your death or Total Disability. All benefits are paid
by Sun Life Assurance Company of Canada (Insurer) to HSBC Bank Canada to be credited 10 your insured mortgage, line of
credit or demand loan. This information sheet is for illustrative purposes only and does not form part of your Certificate.

Insurance coverage is subject to limitations and exclusions. Please review the details and requirements of coverage
carefully before you apply.

Benefits
Life Insurance pays the qualifying balance of an insured mortgage, line of credit or demand loan in the event of death
(up to $750,000). The gualifying balance is determined as follows:

Mortgagef(s): If the mortgage amount is less than or equal to $750,000 (at the time of enrolment), the qualifying
balance is (i} for blended payment mortgages, the outstanding principal balance (excluding principal or interest in
arrears), or (i) for interest-only mortgages, the outstanding principal balance (excluding interest in arrears), less
an amount equal to the principal payments that would have been made on a blended mortgage with an equal
opening balance based on the same interest rate and amortization period as your interest-only mortgage. If the
mortgage amount is greater than $750,000, the qualifying balance is adjusted based on the ratio established as
your amount of insurance upon enrolment.

Line of Credit or Demand Loan: The qualifying balance for an insured line of credit or demand loan is the lesser
of (i) the outstanding balance on the date of death, (ii) the average debit balance for the 12 months preceding the
date of death, or (ili} the Loan Amount insured shown on your Application.

Disability Insurance pays the minimum monthly payment in the event of a disability (up to $4,000 per month} for a
maximum of 24 months {in aggregate). In all cases, only one disability benefit will be paid at any one time. The benefit
will continue until the insured is no longer disabled or the maximum 24-month benefit period is reached. Disability
Insurance is not available on any mortgage or line of credit with an interest-only repayment option. Demand Loans with
HSBC Bank Canada are not eligible for disability insurance under Policy 57305.

Eligibility and Pre-Existing Conditions
Life Insurance Eligibility: You must be between the ages of 18 and 64 on the date of application.

Disability Insurance Eligibility: You must also have Life Insurance (under Policy 57905) and be actively at work for 20
hours or more per week on the date of application.

Pre-Existing Conditions: Please be advised that no insurance benefit is paid if death orTotal Disability is directly
or indirectly caused or contributed to by a Pre-Existing Condition {(and death orTotal Disability occurs in the
first 12 months of coverage). A “Pre-Existing Condition” is a condition or health problem for which you consulted
with or received advice, treatment, care and/or service from a Licensed Medical Professional or you took medications
or injections in the 12 months before becoming insured.

What Is Not Paid
No benefit is paid If death or Total Disability is directly or indirectly caused or contributed to by:;

« a Pre-Existing Condition (defined above), if your death or Total Disability occurs in the first 12 months of coverage;

« suicide;

+ an air travel accident, unless a fare-paying passenger or acting as a crew member of a regularly scheduled
commercial passenger airline flight,

» active participation in a civil disarder or war {unless on active military duty with the Canadian Armed Forces or
Reserve): or

* events which occur while you are committing or attempting to commit a criminal act.

1019107-E_2014-02 Page 1¢i 3 In addition, no benefit is paid if Total Disability is directly or indirectly caused or contributed to by:

normal pregnancy (this exclusion does not apply to complications of pregnancy); or
* an intentionally self-inflicted injury.

When Your Coverage Begins and Ends

The insurance becomes effective on the later of: a) the date the application is signed by you; b) the date your funds are

advanced by HSBC Bank Canada: or ¢} the date written approval is granted by Insurer (in cases where the Application
requires written approval).

Coverage automatically ends on the earliest of: a) the date the insured mortgage, line of credit or demand loan is paid
in full or refinanced; b) the date of an insured person’s death: ¢) the date you turn /70 years of age (coverage continues
on younger insured, if any); d) the date your written request to cancel is received by HSBC Bank Canada; e) when vour
premiums are 60 days in arrears or payment under your insured mortgage, line of credit or demand loan is 60 days in
arrears; 1) when Policy 57905 ends; g} for life insurance, when the maximum benefit is paid, h} for disability, upon the

earlier of 24 monthly payments being paid on your behalf, the date life insurance is continued under Prior Coverage
Recognition or the date life insurance ends.

What Coverage Costs

Rates are determined based on the age of the borrower at the time of application (Mortgages) or on the payment due date
(Lines of Credit/Dermand Loans). Joint coverage rates are based on the age of the oldest insured. Premiums are calculated

and charged at the same frequency as the regular payment under the insured credit facility. Provincial sales taxes on
insurance premiums will be added, if applicable. The following outlines current rates (applicable at time of application).

Life Insurance

Lines of Credit/Demand Loans under $50,000: For lines of credit and demand loans under $50,000 the applicable

rates are $0.50 per 1,000 for single coverage and $0.85 per $1,000 for joint coverage regardless of your age at date
of application. The monthly premium payable is calculated on the first day of the month by applying the rate to the
previous month's average daily debit balance. Example: If coverage is joint and your average daily debit balance for
the preceding month was $10,000, your premium payable = $8.50 calculated as follows: {$10,000 + 1,000) X 0.85.

Continuing Professional Development (CPD) Program
MANDATORY REPORTING REQUIREMENT

m
for Engmeermg or Geoscience. Not Applrcable to Students, Applicants, Members-wm-Trammg, Life
R Members or those with Non-Practicing Status. *

1. Reporting Your Professional Development Hours (PDHs)

If you are a Professional Member, Licensee, or Professional Licensee, you must report your CPD hours
annually. You must submit a minimum of 240 hours over three years and have reported hours in at least three of

the six categories each year. Refer to the CPD Program Guideline available on APEGA’s web site at
hitps://www.apega.ca/members/cpd/ for further details.



Please submit your hours prior to the due date of the invoice for your membership dues. Login to Member
Self-Service Centre using your Member Number and Password to submit the CPD hours online.

2. Consequences of Non-Compliance

You are also required to maintain a detailed record of your professional development activities and produce it
when the practice review board (PRB) of APEGA requests it for a review. If you do not submit your CPD hours in
a timely manner as required and fail to produce the detailed activity record upon a request by the PRB, your
registration will be cancelled after 30 days' notice, in accordance with the Regulations under the Engineering and
Geoscience Professions Act.

3. Exception

If you are not currently practicing engineering or geoscience, you may file a written declaration to change your
status to ‘non-practicing’. The declaration form is available at hitps://www.apega.ca/members/changes/; the
completed form should be submitted to cpd@apega.ca. The declaration is valid only for one year from the date
of the declaration. ‘Non-practicing’ members are exempt from the mandatory CPD program requirement outlined
above, but are not exempt from paying member dues.



Please note that practicing is not considered as being limited to stamping professional documents; it
includes acting as a Responsible Member for an APEGA Permit and all activities contained in the
definitions of "practice" under the Engineering and Geoscience Professions Act.

4. Resuming Active Practice (Going Back to Practicing)

If you had previously declared yourself to be ‘non-practicing” and intend to resume practice, you must obtain
permission from the PRB. To do so, you must submit a completed Application for Permission to Resume
Practice available at https://www.apega.ca/members/changes/. Upon review of the application, the PRB may
require you to comply with certain conditions that it might set prior to allowing you to resume practicing.

5. Requesting Special Consideration

If you are not able to meet the requirements of the CPD program because you are employed part-time,
unemployed, on dues deferment, on parental-maternity leave, in a full-time educational program or have
health/disability issues, you may qualify for special consideration to have your required PDHs reduced. The
request form is available at hitps://www.apega.ca/members/cpd/.



Revised February 2017

Borrower Notification: Freddie Mac Has Purchased Your Mortgage Loan

This letter is for informational purposes only. No action is required on your part.

What You Need to Know

. Your mortgage loan on 14 MANGIA TOWER CT, MISSOURI CITY, TX 77459-1169 was sold to Freddie

Mac on September 21, 2020. Selling mortgage loans to Freddie Mac is a standard part of the mortgage
business for many of the nation’s mortgage lenders. The sale of your mortgage loan to Freddie Mac does
not affect any term, payment, or condition of the mortgage, deed of trust, or note.

Your Servicer is the company to which you currently make your mortgage payments. This may or may not
be the same company who made your mortgage loan. Your Servicer at the time of this notification is

AMERIHOME MORTGAGE COMPANY, LLC, CUSTOMER SERVICE DEPARTMENT PO BOX 77404,
EWING, NJ 77404, (855) 501-3035.

If your name(s) or address requires any corrections, or if you have any questions about your payments,
please contact your Servicer.

Please continue to make your payments to your current Servicer as you do today. When or if there is a
change in who collects your payments, your Servicer will contact you and provide necessary guidance. Do
not send your mortgage payments to Freddie Mac, as we do not service mortgage loans.

Partial Payment
Freddie Mac’s partial payment policy permits the Servicer to do any of the following:

° it may accept a partial payment (a payment that is less than the full amount due) and apply it
to your mortgage loan,

° it may hold a partial payment in a separate account until you pay the rest of the payment, and
then apply the full payment to your mortgage loan, or
° it may refuse to accept any partial payments.

If you wish to make a payment that is less than the full amount due for your regularly scheduled monthly
payment, you may contact your Servicer to discuss how it will treat a partial payment from you.

If this loan is sold, your new lender/owner may have a different partial payment policy.

Please keep a copy of this notice with your other mortgage documents because the sale of your
mortgage loan to Freddie Mac has not been publicly recorded.

Schlumberger Canada Retirement and Savings Program

My Defined Contribution Pension Plan (DCPP)





y 4 Why do fees matter?

All investment funds charge Fund Management Fees (FMFs). FMFs include:

16424

* Investment management fees {IMFs): IMFs pay for professional investment managers to select the
underlying fund's investments and build the fund's portfolio. These fees also pay for the recordkeeping of
your account and member servicing costs. ,

+ Operating expenses: These expenses are generally for the buying and selling of securities for a fund, as well
as any expenses relating to the operation of a fund at both the underlying and segregated fund level.
Operating expenses are charged directly to the fund and included in the calculation of the daily unit value.

Schlumberger Canada pays the IMFs en your behalf in your DCPP and DPSP - you are only responsible for the
operating expenses. This means more of your hard-earned contributions remain in your account for your
retirement.

You are responsible for the full FMFs in your RRSP and TFSA. The fees you pay in the plan are generally much
lower than what you would pay as an individual at a bank or a mutual fund company.

To view the fees that you pay in each of the products you participate in, sign in to
www.mysunlife.ca/schlumberger using your access ID and password, then select 'my financial centre’ >
Accounts » Account Fees.







Changes to Sun Life Financial 2015 Granite® Target Date Fund

The Sun Life Financial 2015 Granite® Target Date Fund matured on June 29, 2015, at which time all assets and
future contributions were automatically transferred to the Sun Life Financial Granite Retirement Segregated
Fund.

“Plan members who held the fund in a non-registered account may experience a capital gain or loss as a result of
the fund maturity. Capital gains must be reported for the tax year the transfer is completed.

You are not required to take any action at this time; however, it's always a good idea to review your current
investment options to ensure that they continue to meet your retirement goals. You can do this by re-visiting
your Investment risk profiler found in your my money@work guide or on www.mysunlife.ca. Through

Morningstar® - a leading provider of investment news and analysis - you can access an overview of the funds in
your plan, including the fund's objective, performance, risk and how the fund is invested.

Locked-out of the Plan Member Services website? You may need to re-register for access,
As a security precaution, if you have not visited Sun Life Financial's Plan Member Services website for a period of 12
months (one year), your online access account is automatically suspended.

To reactivate your account, simply contact the Customer Care Centre number listed on the front page of your
statement. When you call, please have your account number handy. Your date of birth will also be requested to
complete the re-registration process.

Options on termination or retirement

Upon termination or retirement from your plan, benefits may be payable to you. Your options will be communicated
to you at the time you terminate or retire. The options available will depend on applicable legislation and plan rules
and may include receiving an annuity, taking a lump sum or transferring to a retirement product such as a pension
plan, registered retirement savings plan or a non-registered savings plan. For further details, please review the plan
summary or booklet provided to you when you joined the plan or contact your plan administrator.

Have you reviewed your statement recently?

is subject to legislation and the rules of your plan which will govern in case of differences. Please advice Sun Life

sponsor reserve the right to correct any errors. For additional information about the details covered in this

statement or about your plan, please go to mysunlife.ca/Schlumberger.

These are fees that you pay to cover administration costs. Annual administration fees reflect the current fees to

at the time you request the services. The administration fees may be amended with the agreement of or upon
notice to your plan sponsor.

Do you know your rights?

As a member of this plan, you have a right to examine information and documents regarding the plan. This includes
the plan document which sets out the plan rules and amendments made to the document, if any. It may also include
such things as the plan's investment policy statement and annual information returns. In addition, pension legislation

may permit a spouse or any other person entitled to a benefit or their agent, to examine certain plan documents.
For details, please contact your Plan Administrator.

Your spouse. Your beneficiary?
If you have a spouse at the time of your death, legislation may require that some or all of the proceeds be paid to
your spouse. Depending on the pension jurisdiction under which your plan is governed, this may not apply if you

and your spouse are living separate and apart on the date of your death or, if permitted by legislation, the death
benefit has been waived. Please ask your plan administrator for details of the legislation which covers your plan.

Registered funds at 71

The value of your account held in registered pension plans, registered retirement savings plans and/or deferred
profit sharing plans must be disbursed by December 3 1st of the year during which you reach the age of 71. You may
use registered funds to obtain an annuity or another prescribed plan such as a Registered Retirement Income Fund,
Life Income Fund, Prescribed Retirement Income Fund or Locked-In Retirement Income Fund (depending on the

pension jurisdiction). Please contact Sun Life Financial or your financial advisor if you need more information or

Glossary of terms used in this statement

Contribution Pension Plan, Registered Retirement Savings Plan or Deferred Profit Sharing Plan that lets you make
investment decisions among two or more investment options. At Sun Life Financial, most of these plans are funded
by a group annuity policy under which insurance company's segregated funds and guaranteed funds are offered,
Other types of investments (GICs from a trust company and employer's stock) may also be offered under the plan. 16432



Personal rates of return — The personal rates of return are calculated monthly using time-weighted methodology.
This method, which is used by other financial institutions such as mutual fund companies, measures the performance
of the investrment manager for the period that your funds are invested with that manager.

With the time-weighted methodology, the personal rates of return summary is calculated at the end of each month

based on the opening balance, closing balance and cash flow activity for the month. The 3-month, year-to-date,

Return Policy
Shipping and Delivery Policy
Products are delivered United States wide using United States Post (Registered Post). Shipping costs are influenced by the size and weight of the product and your location, exact shipping
costs are calculated in the shopping cart and will be added to the order total before checkout.
Orders are typically shipped in 3-5 business days and shipping times are estimated at between 7-10 business days depending on your location within United States. However, due to the
COVID-19 situation, order processing and fulfillment times may be delayed in some cases. We appreciate your patience. Please be aware deliveries outside of metropolitan areas may take
longer. This service will require your signature when the parcel is delivered. If you are not available at time of delivery, a card will be left for you to collect your parcel from the nearest
Post Office.
Customer Service Policy
Sugar Bottom Bikes is committed to providing exceptional customer service and quality products. We endeavour to make sure that all products listed are currently in stock and pricing is
true and correct. Standard delivery time frames are between 3-10 business days, however due to COVID-19 there may be significant delays to order processing/fulfillment times; in the
event that an ordered item is not available or we are unable to fulfill your order we will notify you within 5 business days to arrange an agreeable alternative item, a back order or a full
refund.
Exchange Policy
Please choose carefully before you buy.
For faulty products, Sugar Bottom Bikes offer a 14 DAY REPLACEMENT WARRANTY, from the date you receive your product. They do not offer a satisfaction guarantee on any of their
products, however due to their high level of customer service, they will always endeavour to keep customers happy and satisfied.
If your product is faulty, it will be replaced with an identical product. If they cannot replace the product, they will offer you the option of choosing another product of the same value, or
provide you with a refund for the total value of the faulty product.
Please note: Standard postage fees apply to all return orders. Where the return relates to a faulty item, the replacement product will be sent out to you, at no charge, within 5 working
days from the date we receive the faulty product.
When returning your product, please make sure you provide the following details:
Your full name
Your order number
Reason why you are returning the product
Your instructions informing us how you would like the issue resolved.
Please include the original order confirmation or invoice you received with your product. Also, if you haven't previously provided a contact phone number, please include this with your
return. This will ensure the issue is resolved quickly, should anyone need to contact you.
